Review:
Nespresso Capsules VertuoLine is definitely an upscale way to have your quick morning shot of frothy coffee. The capsule concept is pretty cool but it is still a limited market so the pricing definitely reflects an exclusive method of coffee drinking.
I am a pour over fan from the old days (1975 Melitta) and French Press so I can enjoy whole bean varieties of my choosing from around the world. There is a work-around to reuse the capsules with our own choice of bean. I do like the recycling measures of Nespresso to reuse the capsules.

)
